To calculate the LIX readability score, we will use the following formula:

LIX = (A + B + 100 * C) / F

Where:
A = the number of words containing 1-3 letters (short words)
B = the number of words containing 4-6 letters (medium words)
C = the number of words containing more than 6 letters (long words)
F = the total number of sentences

First, we will translate and count the words in the text:

