Short words (1-3 letters): 22
Medium words (4-6 letters): 15
Long words (more than 6 letters): 20

The text has 3 sentences. 

Now, computing the score:
A = 22 (short words)
B = 15 (medium words)
C = 20 (long words)
F = 3 (total sentences)
 
LIX = (22 + 15 + 100 * 0.2 * 20) / 3 
LIX = (37 + 400) / 3
LIX = 437 / 3 
LIX ≈ 146

However, an important note on this method, LIX scores can sometimes exceed or dip under expectations due to its scoring style, therefore is  not entirely precise in its scoring results.